# Frontend — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` for local overrides, or set these in Netlify/Vercel/Railway.

# Where the API lives. Leave unset in dev (uses Vite's /api proxy → localhost:4000).
# In production, point to your API's public URL. Without this, /api requests resolve
# to the frontend host (returning the SPA HTML), the JSON parse fails, and the
# stat tiles + photo carousel show their em-dash / "no rooms" fallbacks.
#
# Examples:
#   Railway (separate services):  VITE_API_BASE=https://assetaplus-room-match-backend-production.up.railway.app
#   Same-origin (Vite + Node on one host):  VITE_API_BASE=
VITE_API_BASE=